#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':"Spike it up or calm it down – this grape-scented texturizing matte wax separates, forms and shapes hard to hold hair. Jacques Hair Jam contains natural Glycerin to eliminate frizz. Hair Jam is alcohol free so it won't dry out hair.Bonjour! My name is Jacques and I am from the country that is famous for the Eiffel Tower and a cathedral called Notre Dame. My family lives on a vineyard in the region of Bordeaux. My twin brother Luc and I love to run through the vines and eat the grapes! We harvest the grapes each September. Do you know where I live? France- "},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':'Cleans and moisturizes hair.Selamat pagi (she-la-maht PAH-gee)! My name is Pia and my country has lots of festivals! On any day of the year, somewhere people are celebrating with special food, costumes, music and dance. We have so many festivals because we come from many different cultures: Muslim, Hindu, Chinese, Dutch and native traditions. The Rice Harvest Festival is my favorite. We celebrate and give thanks for rice by painting the village and decorating it with flags and rice-god dolls. Do you know where I live?- '},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':'Smoothes and detangles hair.Buenos días! My name is Rosa and the capital of my country is Madrid. I don’t live near Madrid, but when I am older, I hope to travel there to perform Flamenco dancing! My family and I live in the southern part of my country in a village where all of the houses are painted white. The Moors built our houses 1,000 years ago! The Moors came to live in my country and built many beautiful things, including an ancient palace called Alhambra. The entire palace has a high wall around it with lookout towers to protect it from invaders! Do you know where I live? Spain- '},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':'WHAT IT IS Tearless shampoo with a fruity pineapple fragrance. WHAT IT DOES Cleans and moisturizes hair. Selamat pagi (she-la-maht PAH-gee)! My name is Pia and puppet theater is popular in my country. My father is a "Dalang " or puppeteer. For my birthday I always ask him to put on a show with special shadow puppets. For hundreds of years shadow puppets have been used in our country to tell Hindu stories. Sometimes the show lasts for hours. "Dalangs" are highly respected in the village because they have the important role of passing down stories and lessons. Being a "dalang" is hard work. He has to move all the puppets speak in different voices and direct the musicians. I am proud of my father and I love to watch his puppet shows! Do you know where I live?'},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':"WHAT IT IS Tearless shampoo with a yummy raspberry fragrance. WHAT IT DOES Cleans and moisturizes hair. ¿Cómo estás? My name is Rosa and my country is the 3rd largest in Europe. I live in the Flamenco capital of my country. There are over 30 styles of Flamenco dancing. Each kind has three parts: Cante the song; Baile the dance; and Guitarra the guitar playing. Each dance and song tells a story. I'm learning a dance about the history of my country. There are thousands of festivals all over my country every year and there is flamenco dancing at many of them. I just got a new flamenco dress! I love the bright color and getting to wear the flower in my hair. When I get older I want to dance as beautifully as my mom. Do you know where I live?"},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':"WHAT IT IS Moisturizing detangler with a fruity banana fragrance. WHAT IT DOES Smoothes and detangles hair. Hola! My name is Bonita. I live in the second largest country in Central America. Tegucigalpa which means Silver Mountain is our capital city. Silver was discovered in my country in the 1500s and is still mined today. The famous explorer Christopher Columbus set foot on the American mainland for the first time in the northern part of my country. He named our country after the deep waters surrounding our coastline. The ocean is full of many kinds of sea life including conchs. A conch is a sea creature that lives in a shell. One of my brothers is learning how to play a conch-shell horn! Music and dance are very popular in my country. I take dance classes with my sisters and some of my friends. We dance to live musicians playing drums and guitars but we don't dance to the conch-shell horn. Do you know where I live? Honduras"},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':"WHAT IT IS Shaping hair gel for children and babies. WHAT IT DOES Shapes molds and sculpts hair to desired style. Morn! My name is Erik. In my country the sun doesn't completely set during parts of the summer - it stays light all night! That's why some people call it the land of the Midnight Sun. Along with really long summer days my country is also famous for Vikings the invention of the paper clip and the Aurora Borealis (Northern Lights) - a humongous natural light show caused by blasts of energy from the sun. I like to get a closer look at them with my telescope! Do you know where I live? Norway"},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':'WHAT IT IS Stronger than a polar bear! Cooler than an igloo! This professional high performance product is perfect for cutting-edge hair styles. WHAT IT DOES This refreshing alcohol-free gel is perfect for icicle spiking chilling slicking or cool sculpting. Nothing holds longer. Hallo! My name is Einar and I live on Europe s second largest island. One third of our 280 000 citizens live in the capital city of Reykjavik. The northernmost part of my country is in the Arctic Circle and the easternmost is close to Norway. My friends and I like to ski sled and even go spelunking in ice caves. Do you know where I live? Iceland'},
#    {'category':'forkids', 'text':'WHAT IT IS Pre-swim conditioner with a tropical coconut fragrance. Outdoor activities like swimming make summer a blast but it also means you have to take extra precautions against hair and skin damage. With Circle of Friends products we make it easy to have fun without the worry! WHAT IT DOES Offers an exclusive blend of polymers emollients and Vitamin B5 that help protect hair from turning green breaking and overall drying caused by pool chemicals or salt water. G day Mate! My name is Kylie and I live in a beach city called Cairns. Our house is close to the Pacific Ocean. The water is warm here so I ve been swimming and snorkeling my whole life. The best places to snorkel are along the Great Barrier Reef. Thousands of different kinds of fish and other animals live on the reef. It s like swimming in a giant aquarium! Where I live swimsuits are called "cozzies " but my cousins in the southern part of our country call them "bathers" or "togs." Nicknamed "the land down under" but my country is also an island and its own continent! Do you know where I live?'},
